 This function takes a string as input and returns the same string with all lowercase characters converted to uppercase and vice versa. Here is how you can implement it in PHP:
```php
<?php
function flipCase($string) {
    $result = "";
    for ($i = 0; $i < strlen($string); $i++) {
        if (ctype_upper(substr($string, $i, 1))) {
            // Character is uppercase, convert to lowercase
            $result .= strtolower(substr($string, $i, 1));
        } elseif (ctype_lower(substr($string, $i, 1))) {
            // Character is lowercase, convert to uppercase
            $result .= strtoupper(substr($string, $i, 1));
        } else {
            // Character is not alphabetic, keep it as-is
            $result .= substr($string, $i, 1);
        }
    }
    return $result;
}
```
In this function, we iterate over each character of the input string and check if it's uppercase or lowercase using `ctype_upper` and `ctype_lower`. If it is uppercase, we convert it to lowercase using `strtolower`, and vice versa. For non-alphabetic characters, we keep them as they are.

Now you can call the function with any string:
```php
$result = flipCase("Hello");
echo $result; // Outputs "hELLO"
```
This code will work for all strings, regardless of their length or content.

